# God's Eye — Deployment Environment Variables Overview
#
# This file is a deployment checklist. The authoritative .env.example files are:
#   - backend/.env.example   (Railway backend service variables)
#   - frontend/.env.example  (Vercel frontend environment variables)
#
# ─── Railway Backend Variables (set in Railway service → Variables) ──────────
#
#   LLM_API_KEY                  Your OpenAI (or compatible) API key
#   GODS_EYE_LLM_PROVIDER        openai | nous | custom (default: openai)
#   GODS_EYE_MODEL               Model name (default: o4-mini)
#   GODS_EYE_MOCK                false in production
#   GODS_EYE_ENV                 production
#   GODS_EYE_DB_PATH             /app/data/gods_eye.db  (volume mount at /app/data)
#   GODS_EYE_LEARNING_SKILL_DIR  /app/skills            (volume mount at /app/skills)
#   GODS_EYE_CORS_ORIGINS        https://your-frontend.vercel.app  (exact Vercel URL)
#   GODS_EYE_LOG_LEVEL           info
#
# ─── Vercel Frontend Variables (set in Vercel → Settings → Env Vars) ────────
#
#   VITE_API_BASE    https://your-railway-backend.up.railway.app/api
#   VITE_WS_BASE     wss://your-railway-backend.up.railway.app
#
# ─── Railway Volume Mounts (set in Railway service → Volumes) ────────────────
#
#   Mount path: /app/data    → SQLite database (gods_eye.db persists across redeploys)
#   Mount path: /app/skills  → SkillStore YAML files (skills persist across redeploys)
#
# ─── Production Verification Checklist ──────────────────────────────────────
#
#   [ ] GET https://your-backend.railway.app/api/health returns 200, mock_mode: false
#   [ ] Vercel frontend loads at /, /welcome, /dashboard without 404
#   [ ] Browser devtools Network tab shows wss:// WebSocket during simulation
#   [ ] Run 5 simulations, redeploy Railway service, reload History — all 5 still present
#   [ ] NSE live data banner absent (or shows "live") when Railway can reach NSE
